UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Victor Daniel HERNANDEZ, Defendant-Appellant. No. 04-40863

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Oct. 25, 2006. James Lee Turner, Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Southern District of Texas, Houston, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. John Riley Friesell, Bellaire, TX, for Defendant-Appellant. Victor Daniel Hernandez, Three Rivers, TX, pro se. Before JOLLY, DeMOSS, and STEWART, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM: *

Counsel appointed to represent Victor Daniel Hernandez on appeal from the revocation of his term of supervised release has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed a brief as is required by Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Hernandez has not responded to counsel’s motion.

Our independent review of the brief filed by counsel and of the record discloses no nonfrivolous issue for appeal. Counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities, and the appeal is DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
